<img class="wp-image-1307577 aligncenter" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Jigawa-State-map.jpg?resize=569%2C438&#038;ssl=1" alt="FG to engage 5,000 youths in Jigawa – Official" width="569" height="438" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Jigawa-State-map.jpg?resize=300%2C231&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Jigawa-State-map.jpg?resize=768%2C591&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Jigawa-State-map.jpg?resize=58%2C45&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Jigawa-State-map.jpg?resize=252%2C194&amp;ssl=1 252w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Jigawa-State-map.jpg?resize=169%2C130&amp;ssl=1 169w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Jigawa-State-map.jpg?resize=560%2C431&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Jigawa-State-map.jpg?w=788&amp;ssl=1 788w" sizes="(max-width: 569px) 100vw, 569px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Jigawa Government says it has secured 37.373 million dollars facility from Islamic Development Bank (IDB) to propel irrigation, livestock production and provide more farming facilities. Governor Muhammad Badaru made this known to newsmen shortly after inauguration of the state Agricultural Integrated Rural Development Programme in Dutse. Badaru said that the scheme, which was aimed at improving economic activities in the state was expected to create direct and indirect employment opportunities to about two million people. “We will support Micro Finance Banks in all the 27 local government areas to enable farmers access loan in an affordable rate. “I am optimistic that, if we fully implement the policy documents of the loan over two million of Jigawa citizens will be taken out of abject poverty,” he said. Badaru, however, said that the facility would help his administration to consolidate on its achievement in agricultural sector. The governor said that part of the money would be used for the rehabilitation and development of 6,000 hectares for irrigation. Badaru said that when these hectares were fully cultivated as planned, the production output was expected to increase rice production with more than 30,000 tonnes in the state annually. He said that part of the loan would be used to enhance productivity and value chain across the agricultural sector. The governor said his administration would embark on the demarcation of cattle routes, thereby improving grazing reserves with the construction of wind mills, solar boreholes to improve posturing for the cattle. Badaru said that government would also embark on capacity building of at least 200 medium and large scale fish farmers and rehabilitation of 27 skills acquisition centres, among others. He said in addition to that the loan would also be used to improve 15 markets, construct two store in each local government for storing agricultural produce. The governor said that the facility would be used to for the construction of road network to link major agricultural producing centres with markets. The state government has made necessary arrangements to export some of the produce from farm to international markets. [NAN)] Vanguard News Nigeria. The governments of Katsina, Kaduna and Jigawa states, Tuesday, appealed to the House of Representatives to approval their various loan requests to enable them execute projects that would impact on the lives of the people. August 2, 2017 In "News" Top on the agenda of Governor Badaru Abubakar is to create a sustainable economy for Jigawa State. To achieve this, he needs resources. That is one of the reasons he is collaborating with fellow governors from across the North to negotiate a loan facility from the Islamic Bank. Abubakar speaks… March 13, 2016 In "Interview" We are not surprised at the dust being raised in the bid by the 